How to run FreeRapid Downloader on Ubuntu 18.04

Install JRE
# apt install openjdk-8-jre
Do not install default-jre because FRD does not enough work with the latest Java runtime(e.g. java11).
If the newer JRE was installed, openjdk-8 can be selected by update-alternatives after.
# update-alternatives --config java

Download FRD binary package for All platforms. 
https://wordrider.net/freerapid/
FreeRapid-0.9u4.ZIP

Unzip the package

Run FRD
# bash frd.sh

Update plugins
Help > Check for new plugins

Enjoy download
